biography.bio: Chiquito was born on March 12, 1928 in Manila, Philippines as Augusto Valdez Pangan. He was an actor and writer, known for Takbo... Peter... Takbo! (1981), Mister Gimmick (1968) and Okey, ka choy (1967). He died on July 2, 1997 in the Philippines.
biography.name: Chiquito

biography.bio: Tange is an actor, known for Voltes V (1977), Barok (1976) and Yari naaaa!... (1971).
biography.name: Tange

biography.bio: Panchito was born on February 25, 1925 in Paco, Manila, Philippines as Alfonso Tagle. He was an actor, known for Dakilang tanga (1968), Sheman: Mistress of the Universe (1988) and Atsay killer buti nga sa'yo (1984). He died in December 1995 in Manila.
biography.name: Panchito

biography.bio: Elizabeth Oropesa is an actress, known for Angelito: Batang ama (2011), Nunal sa tubig (1976) and In the Navel of the Sea (1998).
biography.name: Elizabeth Oropesa

biography.bio: Born to Gonzalo Teodosio and Maria Maximo in Feb 19, 1929, Gavino Maximo Teodosio entered Filipino cinema when it was reaching its so-called "Golden Age." Using the screen name "Max Alvarado" for dramatic appeal, he played his first bit role in Halik sa Banila (1948) and his first starring role in Alias Chain Gang (1967). Alvarado built his own brand of villain in seriocomic manner that was many times imitated. He appeared in other films like Totoy Gwapo (1970); James Bondat (1970), a send-up on the James Bond films; Deadly Fighter (1970); Liezl at ang Seven Hoods (1971); Mahiwagang Kris (1976); Sebastian Gustavo (1971); Jailbreak (1972); El Vibora (1972) and Nardong Putik (1972). Alvarado won the Filipino Academy of Movie Arts & Sciences (FAMAS) best supporting award for Ang Kampana Sa Santa Quiteria (1971). The same year, he received a trophy for best supporting performance at the 2nd Quezon City Film Festival, for Alyas Bagsik (1971). He was nominated by the FAMAS as best supporting actor for Pitong Makasalanan (1962) and Tiger Unit (1963). With his death, it was never the same again for villainy in Filipino cinema.
biography.name: Max Alvarado
